      <title>Re: set sort_by parameter properly</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezsearchpro/forum/general/set_sort_by_parameter_properly/re_set_sort_by_parameter_properly</link>
      <description>Thanks, I'll add it.&#13;
&#13;
You can also use several sort_by values like other fetch functions:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
   {set search=fetch(content,search,&#13;
                     hash(text,$search_text,&#13;
                          class_id,$search_class_array,&#13;
                          sort_by, array( array('ranking',false()), array('published',false())),&#13;
                          offset,$view_parameters.offset,&#13;
                          limit,$page_limit))}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (André R)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezsearchpro/forum/general/set_sort_by_parameter_properly/re_set_sort_by_parameter_properly</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Jun 2010 06:57:59 +0000</pubDate>
